title: Jacksonville State totals 619 yards of offense in 42-13 win over Tennessee Tech
text:
Jacksonville State totals 619 yards of offense in 42-13 win over Tennessee Tech THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   10:25   10:25   
Subjects: 
Tennessee (480) 
COOKEVILLE, Tennessee â€” Eli Jenkins passed for two TDs and ran for another and Jacksonville beat Tennessee Tech 42-13 on Saturday. 
Jenkins was 18 of 27 for 184 yards, with scoring strikes of 4 yards to Dalton Screws and 30 yards to Troymaine Pope. Jenkins gained 86 yards on 10 carries and put the Gamecocks up 14-3 on a 40-yard run. 
Jacksonville (5-1, 3-0 Ohio Valley) had 619 yards of total offense, topping the 400-yard mark for a school-record 17th straight game. 
Miles Jones scored on a 45-yard run, Jojo Wynn had a 65-yard score and Josh Clemons scored from 3 yards out. 
Monty Young sacked Colby Brown in the end zone for a safety after the Golden Eagles got the ball after a goal-line stand. 
John Arnold kicked field goals of 43 and 29 yards for Tennessee Tech (2-5, 1-3) and Dorian Carter scored on a 1-yard run.
